      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's just the math working in its favor for the lender, not a hidden fee or a trick in the calculation. Once you fully understand the amortization logic, the \"vanishing\" money is simply the cost of borrowing that specific amount over time. However, if you are seeing an unexpectedly high final balance or higher payments, you should always check your loan documents for any late fees or origination charges.\n\nThe good news is that once you reach the point where your payment covers the interest entirely, every single cent you send will finally go toward paying down your principal. This shift is why refinancing or making extra payments early in the term can be so effective at shortening the life of your loan.",
