      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"trap\" you're feeling is a classic feature of standard amortization, not necessarily a hidden fee, though some lenders do add origination fees that can increase your total interest cost. To combat the momentum of the debt eating your payments, the most effective strategy is to make extra principal payments whenever possible, which instantly reduces the interest charged on future months. Alternatively, refinancing to a lower interest rate can shift that balance, allowing a larger portion of your monthly payment to go toward the principal sooner.",
